ENTRY            M0540   20260120   20260226   20260226       M143
SUBENT        M0540001   20260120   20260226   20260226       M143
BIB                 14         41
TITLE      Gamma-ray absorption by iron nuclei in the giant
           resonance region.
AUTHOR     (B.S.Dolbilkin,A.I.Isakov,V.I.Korin,L.E.Lazareva,
             N.V.Linkova,B.A.Tulupov)
INSTITUTE  (4RUSLEB)
REFERENCE  (J,SNP,9,391,1969)
            English translation of YF,9,675,1969.
INC-SOURCE (BRST)
FACILITY   (SYNCH,4RUSLEB)
SAMPLE     Natural mixture ferrum sample, 90 g/cm**2.
METHOD     (EXTB)
DETECTOR   (BPAIR) Nine-channel magnetic pair spectrometer.
ANALYSIS   Photoabsorption cross section was obtained by
            subtraction of the atomic absorption cross section
            from the measured sum of atomic and nuclear
            absorption cross sections.
REL-REF    (R,,K.Siegbahn,B,SIEGBAHN,,,1955) Atomic absorption
            cross section.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Root-mean-squared  errors  are   given. No
            information on -data-err  and  +data-err  values for
            integrated cross section data.
COMMENT    The total nuclear cross section of gamma-quanta
            absorption in Fe in the energy region 10 - 26.5 MeV
            was measured by the absorption method. The
            measurements were performed with the bremsstrahlung
            spectrum of gamma-emission (Eg-max=260 MeV) on the
            Pian synchrotron. Photons were detected by a
            nine-channel magnetic pair spectrometer with the
            resolution about 1%. The integral cross section at
            10 - 26.5 MeV was found to be 735 +12 -50 mb*MeV. The
            integral cross section at 10 - 26.5 MeV is equal to
            735 (-50,+120) and exhausts about 65% of classical
            dipole sum rule value.
HISTORY    (19980918C) Data were prepared in the MSU INP CDFE by
            V.V.Varlamov.
           (20121104A) SD: Updated to new date formats,lower
            case. Corrected according last EXFOR rules and Dict.
            Ref. on transl. was added. VV: ERR-ANALYS, STATUS,
            HISTORY.
           (20260120A) Corrected by VV and SD: REFERENCE,
            REACTION, STATUS.
ENDBIB              41
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           44
